title: Live AFL: Sunday Round 19
text:
ESSENDON has held its advantage over a sloppy GWS side and leads by eight points at half time at Spotless Stadium.
Neither team has been able to stamp their authority on the contest, with the Bombers looking slightly cleaner and taking a narrow lead as a result.
Brent Stanton has been the leading ball-winner with 16 disposals, while Stephen Coniglio has 13 touches for GWS.
FOR FULL LIVE HQ COVERAGE WITH SUPERCOACH SCORES TAP ON THE GAME IN THE SCORE CENTRE ABOVE OR HERE IF YOU ARE ON A MOBILE DEVICE
IN Sunday’s twilight fixture, St Kilda faces the ladder leaders in Fremantle at Etihad Stadium.
Despite contrasting positions on the ladder, the Saints have won their last two matches against the Dockers by an average margin of 65 points.
There were no late changes for either side, with Nathan Wright (Saints) and Lachie Weller (Dockers) the starting substitutes.
NORTH Melbourne survived a minor scare from an inspired Melbourne outfit, running out 35-point winners at the MCG on Sunday.
After the Kangaroos led by 34 points at quarter-time, the Demons challenged the Kangaroos, booting nine goals to five in the second and third terms.
But five goals to Lindsay Thomas and seven goals in the final term saw the Kangaroos home.
Sunday’s AFL Action (AEST):
Melbourne v North Melbourne at the MCG (1.10pm)
GWS v Essendon at Spotless Stadium (3.20pm)
St Kilda v Fremantle at Etihad Stadium (4.40pm)
